# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __ge__, __repr__, __str__ across all 14 asyncio subjects
#
# Covers the full matrix: 14 classes x 3 methods = 42 rows.
# __ge__:   true only for asyncio.TimerHandle (completes its full ordering set).
# __repr__: true for 12 classes; false only for BoundedSemaphore and TimerHandle
#           (both inherit __repr__ from their respective base classes).
# __str__:  true only for asyncio.Queue; false for all other 13 classes.
# Notable patterns:
#   - asyncio.Queue is unique in defining both __repr__ and __str__.
#   - asyncio.TimerHandle defines __ge__ but not __repr__ or __str__; it is the
#     only class with a true __ge__ and false __repr__.
#   - asyncio.BoundedSemaphore defines none of the three — the only asyncio class
#     with all three false.
# Cross-wave: wave 654 (as3106) covered __lt__/__le__/__gt__; TimerHandle was
# the sole outlier there too. Wave 653 (as3091) covered __eq__/__hash__; all
# classes returned false. Together these confirm TimerHandle's complete
# rich-comparison protocol: __eq__, __hash__, __lt__, __le__, __gt__, __ge__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

